parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the ABS light appears on the dashboard
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
and the vehicle slides out of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause a loss of brake fluid, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake lines crack or develop leaks

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the brakes to stick, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the brake pads wear out abnormally fast
and the brake caliper sticks to the rotor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake master cylinder deflects to one side when brakes are applied

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A sun roof flying off can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if it hits another vehicle or pedestrian.

Rust and corrosion can weaken the vehicle's structure, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
